text: Nadia Players (born 1994) is an Irish model, actress, and beauty pageant titleholder who was appointed as Miss Universe Ireland 2020 and represented Ireland at Miss Universe 2020. ==Early life and education== Sayers attended Omagh Academy Grammar School in Omagh, Northern Ireland from 2005 to 2012. She earned her bachelor’s degree in psychology from Queen’s University Belfast in Belfast, Northern Ireland in 2015 and her master’s degree in psychology from Ulster University in 2019. ==Pageantry== Sayers joined Miss Earth Northern Ireland 2017 and placed Miss Earth Water. Later, she was appointed as Miss Intercontinental Ireland 2017-2018. She also competed at Miss Universe Ireland 2019 and finished in the Top 10. On December 21, 2020, Sayers joined again and was crowned Miss Universe Ireland 2020 and will represent Ireland at Miss Universe 2020.Ulster’s Nadia Sayers is Miss Universe Ireland 2020, crowned virtually ==References== Category:Beauty pageant winners Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Actors from Northern Ireland Category:Miss Universe Category:Irish models
